        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 16 at 7:15PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 715 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 13
miles west of Wolf Creek, or 30 miles northwest of Helena, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wolf Creek, Canyon Creek, and Craig.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
